title: Polling shows that most US voters say economic concerns are top of mind
description: Economic issues remain a top concern for most voters ahead of the 2022 election, a review of recent polling finds, with many also worried about America's democratic process itself. But voters' highest priorities are divided along partisan lines, with abortion rights continuing to resonate strongly for Democrats, while Republicans remain sharply focused on inflation. Concerns about other issues, from gun policy to immigration, are often similarly polarized. And some topics that drew attention in previous elections -- like the coronavirus pandemic -- are relatively muted this year.
